"{\"uid\": \"straitstimes.com-sport-japan-leukaemia-survivor-rikako-ikee-to-swim-at-paris-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Choose edition  Search  singapore  asia  world  opinion  life  business  sport  Visual  Podcasts  SPH Rewards  STClassifieds  Paid press releases  Advertise with us  FAQs  Contact us  Sign up now:Get the biggest sports news in your inbox  Rikako Ikee (front row, second from left) was a member of the Japanese women's 4x100m freestyle relay team that won silver at the Asian Games in 2023.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 389, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 98, \"end\": 101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6526186269877824e-13, \"text\": \"SPH\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\"}, {\"begin\": 147, \"end\": 156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"score\": 0.9604822703099307, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Advertise\", \"types\": [\"Q7377\", \"Q729\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\"}, {\"begin\": 239, \"end\": 250, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rikako_Ikee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rikako Ikee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rikako_Ikee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rikako_Ikee\"}, {\"begin\": 301, \"end\": 309, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9973095333870735, \"rank\": 0.002579971781785851, \"text\": \"Japanese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"PHOTO: ST FILE  Published\\u00c2Mar 28, 2024, 05:47 PM  Updated\\u00c2Mar 28, 2024, 09:09 PM  TOKYO\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093Leukaemia survivor Rikako Ikee will compete for Japan in the 100m butterfly at the Paris Olympics after missing out on an individual place at the Tokyo Games in 2021.\", \"from\": 391, \"to\": 647, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 500, \"end\": 511, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rikako_Ikee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rikako Ikee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rikako_Ikee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rikako_Ikee\"}, {\"begin\": 529, \"end\": 534, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9999999652700359, \"rank\": 3.254912650046695e-08, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Three-time world champion Daiya Seto will swim the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 200m individual medley after Japan\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s swimming federation announced its 27-member team for the Paris Games on March 27.\", \"from\": 649, \"to\": 828, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 675, \"end\": 685, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daiya_Seto\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Daiya Seto\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daiya_Seto\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daiya_Seto\"}, {\"begin\": 747, \"end\": 755, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Para_swimming\", \"score\": 0.9999349003623554, \"rank\": 6.510387593689057e-05, \"text\": \"swimming\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Para_swimming\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Para_swimming\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An 18-year-old Ikee was named Most Valuable Player of the 2018 Asian Games after claiming six golds and two silvers, and was expected to be one of the stars of the Tokyo Olympics.\", \"from\": 830, \"to\": 1009, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 860, \"end\": 880, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Most_valuable_player\", \"score\": 0.9999973286839331, \"rank\": 2.2815856021404363e-06, \"text\": \"Most Valuable Player\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Most_valuable_player\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Most_valuable_player\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In early 2019, a few months after those triumphs, she was diagnosed with leukaemia and spent around 10 months in hospital.\", \"from\": 1011, \"to\": 1133, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She returned to competition only in August 2020 and completed an incredible comeback by winning the 100m freestyle and 100m butterfly at the 2021 Olympic trials.\", \"from\": 1135, \"to\": 1296, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her times were not fast enough to qualify for the individual events in Tokyo, but the performances gained her selection for both freestyle and medley relay teams at her home Olympics.\", \"from\": 1298, \"to\": 1481, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1369, \"end\": 1374, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7460016177278656e-14, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now 23, Ikee secured her place in the 100m butterfly by just 0.01 of a second at Japan\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s trials earlier in March as she held off the fast-finishing Shiho Matsumoto to finish second in 57.30sec.\", \"from\": 1483, \"to\": 1678, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1639, \"end\": 1648, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matsumoto_Domain\", \"score\": 0.9944242345409392, \"rank\": 0.005483526545244344, \"text\": \"Matsumoto\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matsumoto_Domain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matsumoto_Domain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIn the end, I think it was my long arms that won the touch,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Ikee was quoted as saying by Olympics.com.\", \"from\": 1680, \"to\": 1788, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1775, \"end\": 1787, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0964642920749506e-14, \"text\": \"Olympics.com\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI think God was on my side today.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Ikee had been training in Australia under coach Michael Bohl, where she has been focusing on increasing the number of dolphin kicks straight after the start of her races, which has been a weak point for her, according to The Japan Times.\", \"from\": 1790, \"to\": 2068, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1857, \"end\": 1866, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.980103806178988, \"rank\": 0.012368247202683973, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 1879, \"end\": 1891, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Bohl\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Michael Bohl\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Bohl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Bohl\"}, {\"begin\": 2052, \"end\": 2067, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Japan_Times\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Japan Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Japan_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Japan_Times\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She said before the trials: \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI am confident I can beat the qualifying times.\", \"from\": 2070, \"to\": 2148, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"My aim is well beyond them.\", \"from\": 2149, \"to\": 2176, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ve improved tremendously.\", \"from\": 2178, \"to\": 2210, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m approaching this meet with the attitude that I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m absolutely going to Paris.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Her 100m fly race was won in an impressive 56.91sec by 17-year-old\\u00c2\\u00a0Mizuki Hirai, one of several talented Japanese teenagers in the team.\", \"from\": 2211, \"to\": 2436, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2367, \"end\": 2373, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shigeru_Mizuki\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7658215409097072e-20, \"text\": \"Mizuki\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shigeru_Mizuki\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shigeru_Mizuki\"}, {\"begin\": 2374, \"end\": 2379, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Masafumi_Hirai\", \"score\": 0.8020135056823948, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hirai\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Masafumi_Hirai\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Masafumi_Hirai\"}, {\"begin\": 2405, \"end\": 2413, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9973095333870735, \"rank\": 0.002579971781785851, \"text\": \"Japanese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Also heading to Paris are Mio Narita, 17, in the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 400m IM and Tomoyuki Matsushita, 18, who swims the same men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s event.\", \"from\": 2438, \"to\": 2567, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2454, \"end\": 2459, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999964734343, \"rank\": 3.526342622011282e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2464, \"end\": 2467, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mio_Shirai\", \"score\": 0.9908228130887412, \"rank\": 0.00702010184460068, \"text\": \"Mio\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mio_Shirai\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mio_Shirai\"}, {\"begin\": 2468, \"end\": 2474, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Narita_International_Airport\", \"score\": 0.9999999919368747, \"rank\": 8.063324177659878e-09, \"text\": \"Narita\", \"types\": [\"Q1248784\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Narita_International_Airport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Narita_International_Airport\"}, {\"begin\": 2518, \"end\": 2528, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Panasonic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.681216775358191e-21, \"text\": \"Matsushita\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Panasonic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Panasonic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cWe have a very balanced group of veterans and the young and those somewhere in the middle,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d said Japan Swimming Federation president Daichi Suzuki, the 1988 Seoul 100m backstroke gold medallist.\", \"from\": 2569, \"to\": 2768, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2671, \"end\": 2696, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_Swimming_Federation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Japan Swimming Federation\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_Swimming_Federation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_Swimming_Federation\"}, {\"begin\": 2707, \"end\": 2720, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daichi_Suzuki\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.617798050924214e-23, \"text\": \"Daichi Suzuki\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daichi_Suzuki\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daichi_Suzuki\"}, {\"begin\": 2731, \"end\": 2736, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999934616426, \"rank\": 6.538409950647985e-09, \"text\": \"Seoul\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI want to see them level up in the next four months and expect that they will show their will to fight in Paris.\", \"from\": 2770, \"to\": 2885, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2879, \"end\": 2884, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999964734343, \"rank\": 3.526342622011282e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I am proud of the athletes we have here.\", \"from\": 2886, \"to\": 2926, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I hope they will raise our flag in Paris.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Meanwhile, British Olympic diving champion Matty Lee, who won gold alongside Tom Daley in 2021, will miss the Paris Games following spinal surgery.\", \"from\": 2927, \"to\": 3120, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2984, \"end\": 2991, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.7305549646487512, \"rank\": 0.3673150136696093, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 3016, \"end\": 3025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matty_Lee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matty Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matty_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matty_Lee\"}, {\"begin\": 3050, \"end\": 3059, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.93680858817784e-55, \"text\": \"Tom Daley\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The British pair won the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s synchronised 10m platform at the Tokyo Olympics and Lee also triumphed alongside Noah Williams at the Commonwealth Games in 2022.\", \"from\": 3122, \"to\": 3284, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3126, \"end\": 3133, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.7305549646487512, \"rank\": 0.3673150136696093, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 3207, \"end\": 3210, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"score\": 0.99577148752689, \"rank\": 0.004246219847904079, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\"}, {\"begin\": 3236, \"end\": 3249, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Williams_(diver)\", \"score\": 0.999998273608197, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Williams\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Williams_(diver)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Williams_(diver)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the 26-year-old will miss the Olympics after receiving treatment.\", \"from\": 3286, \"to\": 3355, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThe surgery went well, but my surgeon told me my nerve was very stuck and it took longer than expected to remove my bulging disc without damaging my nerve,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d he said in an Instagram post.\", \"from\": 3357, \"to\": 3548, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3533, \"end\": 3542, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.8078586735610545e-22, \"text\": \"Instagram\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cHe also told me it wouldn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t have got better on its own, so to have the surgery was the right decision.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Lee added: \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cWhat this means for me this year is self-explanatory, which is very sad, but the reason I look so damn happy in hospital is that I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m no longer in chronic pain.\", \"from\": 3550, \"to\": 3837, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3662, \"end\": 3665, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"score\": 0.99577148752689, \"rank\": 0.004246219847904079, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ve found a solution and I have something to work on.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Daley, 29, still has a chance of winning a second straight Olympic gold after joining forces with Williams.AFP  Olympics 2024  Swimming  Japan  Cancer  Olympics  E-paper  Newsletters  Podcasts  RSS Feed  About Us  Terms & Conditions  Personal Data Protection Notice  Need help?\", \"from\": 3838, \"to\": 4177, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4027, \"end\": 4035, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Para_swimming\", \"score\": 0.9997030015861095, \"rank\": 0.0002941465888325531, \"text\": \"Swimming\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Para_swimming\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Para_swimming\"}, {\"begin\": 4037, \"end\": 4042, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9999999652700359, \"rank\": 3.254912650046695e-08, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}, {\"begin\": 4062, \"end\": 4069, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Electronic_paper\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"E-paper\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Electronic_paper\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Electronic_paper\"}, {\"begin\": 4094, \"end\": 4102, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"RSS Feed\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RSS\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reach us here.\", \"from\": 4178, \"to\": 4192, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertise with us\", \"from\": 4194, \"to\": 4211, \"entities\": []}]}"